      "content": "it's more than just \"mood\" though. whenever the pulse hits, it's like a wave of anxiety hits everyone on my block at the same time. i saw my neighbor staring out his window looking totally lost, just frozen. it's almost like they're testing something. if someone wanted to keep a population calm or even just keep them on edge without them knowing why, wouldn't using the existing grid to transmit these kinds of waves be the perfect way to do it?",
